 By Shina Abubakar A young man, Oduola Mutiu was on Monday sentenced to three months in prison by Magistrate Risikat Olayemi of an Osogbo Magistrate court in Osun state for stealing two goats. The convict was said to have stolen a goat valued N30,000 and another she-goat valued N15,000, a property of one Oluwatoyin Dada. According to the charge, the culprit stole one of the goats sometimes in March 2019 at about 15:47pm. Continue reading Man bags three months jail term for stealing two goats at Vanguard Nigeria. Source: Vanguard